article.headline: IUPUI 95, UMKC 59
article.story: INDIANAPOLIS (AP) -- Matt Burks scored a game-high 25 points to lead IUPUI to a 95-59 victory over Missouri-Kansas City on Saturday in the Mid-Continent Conference. The Jaguars (11-7, 6-1 MCC) took the lead on David Barlow's layup 53 seconds into the game and never trailed. IUPUI led by as many as 31 points before taking a 47-23 lead at the half. IUPUI built its lead after holding UMKC (8-10, 5-3) to 22 percent shooting in the half. The Kangaroos hit just three of their 13 3-point attempts. George Hill finished with 23 points, 10 rebounds and six assists for the Jaguars. He was 10-for-10 from the field. Barlow scored 13, while Brandon Cole added 10 and a game-high 14 rebounds two nights after becoming the school's fifth all-time leading rebounder. Matt Huppe led the Kangaroos with 15 points and four assists. Quinton Day was UMKC's only other player in double figures with 11 points. Dee Ayuba scored nine points and had four rebounds.
